message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - This paper is about using deep learning for medical image analysis, specifically for pulmonary lobe segmentation in CT scans. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning and the proposed loss function suggest that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The focus on medical imaging and disease diagnosis further suggests that it could belong to the Medical Imaging (cs.MED) category. Finally, the use of neural networks and the focus on image segmentation suggest that it could also belong to the Neurons and Cognition (cs.NEURON) category.
